spanGrp.span: they are locked in a camp.
People teach them how to fight in the war;
Pe të jie-wa ĩã í kashe-gẽ jie-wa ĩã ñã kbö-glö gerra
Jie-wa tsõ mõglö ra jirö ra
They sleep; people made beds for them; they sleep on them.
Jie-wa köpö-gẽ pe-wa jaka yulei ĩã Jeska jie-wa köpö-gẽ
Half of them are sad; the other half isn’t because they are fed;
Jie-wa (hm) moska-wa jẽr iar-ku-gẽ-wa moska-wa kai Pe të í chewẽ-gẽ jela moska/
the others are not fed and thus become sad.
e-gla ka chewẽ kuna pe të Jie jẽr iar-gẽ-wa tã'ĩ (_)
One pretends he is eating something and put something small into his teeth.
Jie jẽk iawã-gẽ-nã jie kajki jirö kötö-ra Jie të jirö jirö yuliski-gla bönẽ kwãwã ka nã
The others give him something, but he doesn’t want it.
Jie jẽk iawã-gẽ siga-wa të jirö mẽ-gẽ ka kianẽ inga
There he goes where the others are;
Jeska jie mĩ-gẽu-mĩ-nẽ mãĩ otro siga-wa tsõ ska
they give him a book and tell him that people say and write thus, so they listen and fight.
Të jie-wa/ jie ĩã juyukwö mẽ-gẽ ska í she-gẽ-nã ñẽbi ñẽbi pe të í she Pe të jirö shte-gẽ jie-wa ĩã-nã jie-wa jie-wa í ksö-glö jie-wa ñã kbö-glö
He becomes sad because of that and because he is very hungry and has nothing to eat.
Je kueinga jie jẽk iar-gẽ-wã tã'ĩ jie ka/ jie bliker-gẽ tã'ĩ jie ka wã jirö ta ñã-nã
So he goes while the others drink wine and things
Je/ ñerö jie mĩ-gẽu-mĩ jeska pe siga-wa të/ tsõ të jirö ye-gẽ kwãwã bino jirö ye-gẽ
So the poor guy stood and and the others sent thing something;
Ñerö jie pobre jẽk kagá të jirö mã'te pe të ĩã
he hid it and wrapped his face up;
Je gugá-wã-ite je blá-wã-ite kepa í wö pabötrá-wã
he hid it and wrapped his face up;
kepa je/ jie të je ñe-gate Ñerö ka í rö ñã-nã
He thus threw it away and hit in the face of a man who was playing the smart alec.
ñerö jie të í báu-mĩ e-gla pekaga kalu kã'kso-gate köũ je bá-wã-ite í wö inga
That man’s face was all covered.
Je_jueta je wö dabá-wã-ite jirö wa
He remained with no food to eat.
Ñerö jie jatanã' jie ka wã jirö (m) ñãnẽ
He was very sad because he has to fight but has not eaten anything.’
